lopment]] unveils Remaking our Heartland plans for Toa Payoh.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/toa-payoh-makeover-to-include-quirky-street-furniture-new-public-housing-projects|title=New public housing projects and mini-dragons in Toa Payoh facelift|last=hermesauto|date=2017-04-22|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2019-04-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180408193838/http://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/toa-payoh-makeover-to-include-quirky-street-furniture-new-public-housing-projects|archive-date=2018-04-08|url-status=live}}</ref>\n**The 10&nbsp;km Tanah Merah Coast Road extension, which has on-road cycling lanes, opens to traffic. The extension replaces the Changi Coast Road, closing for [[Changi Airport|airport]] expansion works.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lim |first1=Adrian |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/new-10km-on-road-cycling-lane-on-extended-tanah-merah-coast-road |title=New 10km on-road cycling lane on extended Tanah Merah Coast Road to open on April 22 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=27 March 2017}}</ref>\n* 27 April - The one-way Sentosa Gateway Tunnel is opened to traffic after a two-year delay. The tunnel can only support cars due to a height constraint of 3.5 metres.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lta.gov.sg/content/ltagov/en/pressroom/sentosa-gateway-tunnel-to-open-on-27-april-2017.html |title=Sentosa Gateway Tunnel to Open on 27 April 2017 |website=LTA |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=3 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Tan |first1=Christopher |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/delayed-sentosa-tunnel-to-open-on-april-27 |title=Delayed Sentosa Gateway Tunnel to open on April 27 |website=The Straits Times |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=3 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Lim |first1=Adrian |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/one-way-sentosa-gateway-tunnel-to-ease-congestion-opens |title=One-way S