est MRT Line]] opens.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chew |first1=Hui Min |title=4 MRT stations on Tuas West Extension to open on June 18 |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/4-mrt-stations-on-tuas-west-extension-to-open-on-june-18 |publisher=The Straits Times |accessdate=6 September 2019 |date=27 April 2017}}</ref>\n* 27 June \u2013 \n**The [[Monetary Authority of Singapore]] will now allow banks to operate or acquire stakes in digital platforms and sell consumer goods and services online. Requirements will also be streamlined for acquisition of complementary non-financial services. However, banks will still not be allowed to venture into property and resort businesses.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mas.gov.sg/news/media-releases/2017/mas-streamlines-framework-for-banks-carrying-on-permissible-non-financial-businesses |title=MAS Streamlines Framework for Banks Carrying On Permissible Non-financial Businesses |website=MAS |date=27 June 2017 |access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1=Yahya |first1=Yasmine |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/banking/singapore-banks-must-innovate-will-be-allowed-to-operate-or-own-consumer-goods-and |title=Singapore banks must innovate; will be allowed to operate or own consumer goods and services online businesses, says Heng Swee Keat |website=The Straits Times |date=27 June 2017 |access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref>\n**At the same time, PayNow is unveiled as a funds transfer service requiring only a mobile or [[National Registration Identity Card|NRIC]] number.<ref name=\"PayNow\">{{Cite web |last1=Lee |first1=Xin En |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/abs-unveils-new-funds-transfer-facility-that-will-require-only-mobile-number-nric |title=ABS unveils new funds transfer facility PayNow which requires only cellphone or identity card number |website=The Straits Times |date=27 June 2017 |access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref>\n* 29 June \u2013 Singapore's 4th desalination plant, the [[Marina East De