|archive-date=24 August 2017|url-status=live|language=en-SG|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n**Several new plans are unveiled. There will be 40,000 more pre-school places by 2022, with new Early Years Centres (EYCs) for children up to 4 years old, leading to MOE Kindergartens catering to children aged 5 and 6. The [[Ministry of Education (Singapore)|Ministry of Education]] will set up 50 kindergartens by 2023 compared to 15 now. In addition, a National Institute of Early Childhood Development will be set up under the [[National Institute of Education]] to raise pre-school teachers' standards.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Goy |first1=Priscilla |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/politics/national-day-rally-2017-more-childcare-places-and-moe-kindergartens-new-institute-for-pre |title=National Day Rally 2017: More childcare places and MOE kindergartens; new institute for pre-school teachers |website=The Straits Times |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=20 August 2017}}</ref> In addition, bilingual education will be emphasised at a young age.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Yong |first1=Charissa |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/national-day-rally-a-boost-in-bilingualism-for-pre-school-pupils |title=National Day Rally 2017: A boost in bilingualism for pre-school pupils |website=The Straits Times |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=20 August 2017}}</ref> Other plans include smart lamp posts as part of the Smart Nation Sensor Platform (SNSP) for surveillance and data collection,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tham |first1=Irene |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/national-day-rally-2017-smart-lamp-posts-to-become-key-nodes-for-surveillance-and-data |title=National Day Rally 2017: 'Smart' lamp posts to become key nodes for surveillance and data collection |website=The Straits Times |access-date=7 November 2019 |date=20 August 2017}}</ref> Parking.sg app to reduce reliance on coupons,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tham |first1=Irene |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/national-day-rally-2017-new-mo