manpower plan announced on 1 October 2016.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Goy |first1=Priscilla |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/new-manpower-plan-for-pre-school-sector-launched-including-skills-focused-initiatives |title=New manpower plan for pre-school sector launched, including skills-focused initiatives |website=The Straits Times |access-date=9 November 2019 |date=1 October 2016}}</ref>\n\n===September===\n* 4 September \u2013 [[Bukit Panjang Bus Interchange]] is officially opened as Singapore's ninth air-conditioned bus interchange.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/new-bukit-panjang-integrated-transport-hub-open-sept-4|title=Bukit Panjang integrated transport hub to open on Sept 4|date=2017-08-08|website=Today|access-date=2019-08-10}}</ref>\n* 11 September \u2013 \n**Former Minister [[Tan Chuan-Jin]] is elected [[Speaker of the Parliament of Singapore]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/tan-chuan-jin-becomes-singapore-s-10th-speaker-of-parliament-9204766|title=Tan Chuan-Jin becomes Singapore\u2019s 10th Speaker of Parliament|date=11 September 2017|work=CNA|access-date=25 July 2019|language=en-SG}}</ref>\n**A new crossover track will be built at [[Canberra MRT station]] to lessen the impact of train service disruptions should they happen.<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Chong |first1=Clara |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/canberra-mrt-station-to-have-crossover-track-to-minimise-train-service-disruptions |title=Canberra MRT station to have crossover track to minimise train service disruptions |website=The Straits Times |access-date=1 November 2019 |date=11 September 2017}}</ref>\n**[[2017 Singaporean presidential election|2017 Presidential Election]]: former [[Speaker of Parliament (Singapore)|Speaker]] [[Halimah Yacob]] is announced by the Presidential Elections Commission as the only candidate issued with both the certificate of eligibility and community certificate.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.str