743.html|title=Lee family feud: MPs call for independent inquiry on abuse of power allegations|last=Yong|first=Nicholas|date=3 July 2017|work=Yahoo News Singapore|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812065102/https://sg.news.yahoo.com/lee-family-feud-mps-call-independent-inquiry-abuse-power-allegations-141913743.html|archive-date=12 August 2017|url-status=live|language=en-SG|access-date=12 August 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> At the end of the debate, no evidence of abuse of power was found.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://in.reuters.com/article/singapore-politics-idINKBN19P0KF|title=Singapore's PM says parliament finds no evidence of abuse of power...|date=2017-07-04|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-04-06|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190125020442/https://in.reuters.com/article/singapore-politics-idINKBN19P0KF|archive-date=2019-01-25|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* 10 July \u2013 \n**PayNow comes into operation.<ref name=\"PayNow\"/>\n**The [[Sungei Road]] flea market is closed for good.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sungei Road Thieves' Market to shut for good on July 10 |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/sungei-road-thieves-market-close-good-july-10 |publisher=Todayonline |date=14 February 2017 |accessdate=14 July 2019}}</ref>\n* 13 July \u2013 [[CapitaLand]] unveils a 280m tower that replaces the Golden Shoe Car Park. It started construction in 2018, later known as CapitaSpring. The building, which will incorporate a park at Market Street, will be completed by 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/182b-tower-to-replace-golden-shoe-car-park|title=$1.82b tower to replace Golden Shoe Car Park|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2019-07-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesstimes.com.sg/companies-markets/market-street-to-get-park-footpaths-from-golden-shoe-car-park-redevelopment|title=Market Street to get park, footpaths from Golden Shoe Car Park redevelopment: Lawrence Wong|website=The Business Times