azon officially launches in Singapore |url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/amazon-officially-launches-singapore |publisher=Todayonline |date=27 July 2017 |accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref>\n* 28 July \u2013 [[NTUC FairPrice|FairPrice]] launches its first unstaffed, cashless Cheers store in [[Nanyang Polytechnic]]. A QR code will be required for access to the store.<ref>{{cite web |title=Launch of The Cheers Unmanned Store at Nanyang Polytechnic |url=https://www.mti.gov.sg/Newsroom/Speeches/2017/07/Speech-by-Minister-Iswaran-at-the-Launch-of-the-Cheers-Unmanned-Store |publisher=MTI |date=28 July 2017 |accessdate=6 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Cheers launches first unmanned, cashless store in Singapore |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/cheers-launches-first-unmanned-cashless-store-in-singapore-9072076 |publisher=CNA |date=28 July 2017 |accessdate=6 August 2019}}</ref>\n* 29 July \u2013 [[East Coast Park]] will be refreshed in upgrading plans announced.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/east-coast-park-to-be-upgraded-with-more-open-spaces-and-amenities|title=East Coast Park to be upgraded with more open spaces and amenities|date=29 July 2017|work=The Straits Times|access-date=5 July 2019|language=en-SG}}</ref>\n\n===August===\n* 1 August \u2013 A ban on [[point of sale display]] of [[tobacco products]] takes effect to reduce the appeal of cigarettes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/health/ban-on-point-of-sale-display-of-tobacco-products-from-aug-1-2017-retailers-will|title=Ban on point-of-sale display of tobacco products from Aug 1, 2017; retailers will have 1-year grace period|date=28 July 2016|work=The Straits Times|access-date=5 July 2019|language=en-SG}}</ref>\n* 4 August \u2013 Professor [[Huang Jing (academic)|Huang Jing]], a Director of Center on Asia and Globalization at [[Lee Kuan Yew School of Public Policy]], becomes the first person known to be permanently banned from Singapore after being accused by the Ministry of Home Affairs for working with a foreign government to influence its foreign policy.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/world/2017/aug/04/singapore-bans-prominent-professor-for-influencing-its-foreign-policy-1638382--1.html|title=Singapore bans prominent professor for influencing its foreign policy|work=The New Indian Express|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812060139/http://www.newindianexpress.com/world/2017/aug/04/singapore-bans-prominent-professor-for-influencing-its-foreign-policy-1638382--1.html|archive-date=2017-08-12|url-status=live|access-date=2017-08-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/08/05/world/asia/singapore-huang-jing.html|title=Singapore Orders Expulsion of American Academic|last=Paddock|first=Richard C.|date=5 August 2017|work=The New York Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190128142508/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/08/05/world/asia/singapore-huang-jing.html|archive-date=28 January 2019|url-status=live|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n*5 August \u2013 A construction worker dies of highly contagious bacterial infection [[diphtheria]], the first case to resurface in 25 years.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.todayonline.com/singapore/construction-worker-21-dies-diphtheria-moh|title=Worker, 21, dies from diphtheria; first local case in 25 years: MOH|date=5 August 2017|work=TODAY|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171021163701/http://www.todayonline.com/singapore/construction-worker-21-dies-diphtheria-moh|archive-date=21 October 2017|url-status=live|language=en|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n*6 August \u2013 [[Our Tampines Hub]] is officially opened.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/our-tampines-hub-opens-featuring-arts-theatre-rooftop-pool-town-9097004|title=Our Tampines Hub opens, featuring arts theatre, rooftop pool, town's largest playground|website=CNA|language=en|access-date=2019-04-06|archive-ur