824074149/http://www.cnn.com/2017/08/20/asia/us-navy-destroyer-collision-singapore/index.html|archive-date=24 August 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> All the bodies are found on 28 August.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tan |first1=Audrey |title=Remains of all 10 sailors missing from USS John S. McCain collision found: US 7th Fleet |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/remains-of-all-10-sailors-missing-from-uss-john-s-mccain-collision-found-us-7th-fleet |website=The Straits Times |date=28 August 2017 |accessdate=19 September 2019}}</ref>\n**Touche, a biometric payment method part of the POSB Smart Buddy programme, will be an option for students to pay for items in school from 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/biometric-payment-system-to-be-an-option-in-schools-in-2018-9142490 |title=Biometric payment system to be an option in schools in 2018 |website=Channel NewsAsia |date=21 August 2017 |access-date=20 November 2019}}</ref>\n* 22 August \u2013 [[Alipay]] will be launched in Singapore.<ref>{{cite web |title=AliPay to launch local wallet for Singapore |url=https://www.todayonline.com/business/impact/alipay-launch-local-wallet-singapore-soon |website=Todayonline |date=22 August 2017 |accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref> Since then, [[Grab (company)|Grab]], [[NETS (company)|NETS]], [[Razer Inc.|Razer]], among other companies have announced plans to set up cashless systems.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ride-hailing app Grab launches e-payment and fund transfer system |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/tech/ride-hailing-app-grab-launches-e-payment-and-fund-transfer-system |website=The Straits Times |date=30 August 2017 |accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"NETSpay\">{{cite web |title=New app lets users pay by Nets \u2013 using their phones |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/new-app-lets-users-pay-by-nets-using-their-phones |website=The Straits Times |date=20 October 2017 |accessdate=13 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=R