{"title_page": "Oda Maria Hove Bogstad", "text_new": "{{short description|Norwegian footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Oda Maria Hove Bogstad\n| fullname       = Oda Maria Hove Bogstad\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| height         = \n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1996|4|24}}\n| birth_place    = [[Moi, Norway]]\n| position       = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| currentclub    = [[Klepp IL]]\n| clubnumber     = 1\n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = \n| youthcaps1     = \n| youthgoals1    = \n| years1         = 2012\u2013\n| clubs1         = [[Klepp IL]]\n| caps1          = 42\n| goals1         = 0\n| years2         = 2016\n| clubs2         = \u2192 [[Amazon Grimstad]] (loan)\n| caps2          = 12\n| goals2         = 0\n| nationalteam1      = Norway U17\n| nationalyears1     = 2013\n| nationalcaps1      = 1\n| nationalgoals1     = 0\n| nationalteam2      = Norway U19\n| nationalyears2     = 2015\n| nationalcaps2      = 1\n| nationalgoals2     = 0\n| nationalteam3      = [[Norway women's national football team|Norway]]\n| nationalyears3     = 2017\u2013\n| nationalcaps3      = 0\n| nationalgoals3     = 0\n| pcupdate       =\n}}\n\n'''Oda Maria Hove Bogstad''' (born 24 April 1996) is a Norwegian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Klepp IL]] in the [[Toppserien]].\n\n==Life and career==\nBogstad started playing football because her dad was a coach and her big sister also played football.<ref>{{cite web|title=1. Oda Maria Hove Bogstad|url=http://kleppil.no/klepp-elite/spillere/1-oda-maria-hove-bogstad/|website=Klepp IL|accessdate=19 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{NFF|3136232}}\n* {{Soccerway|oda-marie-hove-bogstad/268490}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Norway squads\n|bg=#EF2B2D\n|fg=#FFFFFF\n|bordercolor=#203060\n|list1=\n{{Norway squad UEFA Women's Euro 2017}}\n{{Norway squad 2019 FIFA Women's World Cup}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hove Bogstad, Oda Maria}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Lund, Norway]]\n[[Category:Norway women's international footballers]]\n[[Category:Norwegian women's footballers]]\n[[Category:Women's association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Klepp IL players]]\n[[Category:Amazon Grimstad players]]\n[[Category:2019 FIFA Women's World Cup players]]\n\n\n{{Norway-footy-goalkeeper-stub}}\n{{Norway-women-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Oda Maria Hove Bogstad\n| fullname       = Oda Maria Hove Bogstad\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| height         = \n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1996|4|24}}\n| birth_place    = [[Moi, Norway]]\n| position       = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| currentclub    = [[Klepp IL]]\n| clubnumber     = 1\n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = \n| youthcaps1     = \n| youthgoals1    = \n| years1         = 2012\u2013\n| clubs1         = [[Klepp IL]]\n| caps1          = 42\n| goals1         = 0\n| years2         = 2016\n| clubs2         = \u2192 [[Amazon Grimstad]] (loan)\n| caps2          = 12\n| goals2         = 0\n| nationalteam1      = Norway U17\n| nationalyears1     = 2013\n| nationalcaps1      = 1\n| nationalgoals1     = 0\n| nationalteam2      = Norway U19\n| nationalyears2     = 2015\n| nationalcaps2      = 1\n| nationalgoals2     = 0\n| nationalteam3      = [[Norway women's national football team|Norway]]\n| nationalyears3     = 2017\u2013\n| nationalcaps3      = 0\n| nationalgoals3     = 0\n| pcupdate       =\n}}\n\n'''Oda Maria Hove Bogstad''' (born 24 April 1996) is a Norwegian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Klepp IL]] in the [[Toppserien]].\n\n==Life and career==\nBogstad started playing football because her dad was a coach and her big sister also played football.<ref>{{cite web|title=1. Oda Maria Hove Bogstad|url=http://kleppil.no/klepp-elite/spillere/1-oda-maria-hove-bogstad/|website=Klepp IL|accessdate=19 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{NFF|3136232}}\n* {{Soccerway|oda-marie-hove-bogstad/268490}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Norway squads\n|bg=#EF2B2D\n|fg=#FFFFFF\n|bordercolor=#203060\n|list1=\n{{Norway squad UEFA Women's Euro 2017}}\n{{Norway squad 2019 FIFA Women's World Cup}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hove Bogstad, Oda Maria}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Lund, Norway]]\n[[Category:Norway women's international footballers]]\n[[Category:Norwegian women's footballers]]\n[[Category:Women's association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Klepp IL players]]\n[[Category:Amazon Grimstad players]]\n[[Category:2019 FIFA Women's World Cup players]]\n\n\n{{Norway-footy-goalkeeper-stub}}\n{{Norway-women-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Red Director", "label": "safe", "comment": "Adding localshort description: \"Norwegian footballer\", overriding Wikidata description \"association football player\" (Shortdesc helper)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oda_Maria_Hove_Bogstad"}
{"title_page": "Blake Jenner", "text_new": "{{short description|American actor and singer}}\n{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Blake Jenner \n| image = Blake Jenner 2013.jpg\n| caption = Jenner in 2013\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1992|8|27}}\n| birth_name = Blake Alexander Jenner\n| birth_place = [[Miami]], Florida, U.S.\n| spouse = [[Melissa Benoist]] ({{abbr|m.|married}} 2013 or 2015;{{efn|Sources disagree as to the year Jenner and Benoist were married. See [[#Personal life|\u00a7Personal life]]}} {{abbr|div.|divorced}} 2017)\n| occupation = {{Flatlist|\n* Actor\n* singer\n* Wife-beater}}\n| years_active = 2010\u2013present\n}}\n'''Blake Alexander Jenner''' (born August 27, 1992)<ref name=\"TVG\">{{cite web |url=http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/blake-jenner/376096 |title=Blake Jenner |publisher=[[TV Guide|TVGuide.com]] |archivedate=May 29, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160529090948/http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/blake-jenner/376096}}</ref><!--Cited source, TV Guide, also confirmed full name Blake Alexander Jenner--> is an American actor and singer. Jenner won the second season of [[Oxygen (TV channel)|Oxygen]]'s ''[[The Glee Project]]'' and, as a result, portrayed [[Ryder Lynn]] on the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] musical comedy-drama series ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]''. He has since had starring and supporting roles in ''[[Everybody Wants Some!! (film)|Everybody Wants Some!!]]'' (2016), ''[[The Edge of Seventeen]]'' (2016), ''[[American Animals]]'' (2018), and ''[[What/If]]'' (2019).\n\n==Early life==\nJenner was born and raised in [[Miami]], Florida, the son of Mitzy and Richard Vernon Jenner. His father is of English, German and French-Canadian descent, and his mother is of Cuban descent, from a family from [[Santiago de Cuba]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mensfitness.com/life/entertainment/blake-jenner-all-american-leading-man-hollywood-needs-right-now-0 |title=Blake Jenner Is the All-American Leading Man Hollywood Needs Right Now |access-date=March 17, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317143927/http://www.mensfitness.com/life/entertainment/blake-jenner-all-american-leading-man-hollywood-needs-right-now-0 |archive-date=March 17, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"TV Marti\">{{cite web |last=Barroso |first=Gina |title=TV Mart\u00ed Noticias \u2014 Blake Jenner: un joven cubanoamericano de Miami triunfa en Hollywood |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y_bBPQ27OYI |website=YouTube. TV Mart\u00ed Noticias|access-date=November 5, 2014 |language=Spanish |date=January 10, 2013}}</ref>\n\nHe grew up interested in music and film and began playing [[drums]] at age nine.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.miami.com/will-local-singeractor-win-glee-project-article |title=Local singer/actor Blake Jenner wins The Glee Project! |date=August 10, 2012 |last=Marr |first=Madeleine |website=Miami.com}}</ref> He attended [[Felix Varela High School]], where he joined the school's drama society Troupe 6162 and played varsity [[High school football|football]] and [[wrestling]]. Stating that he was \"in love with improv and comedy\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wetpaint.com/glee/articles/glee-projects-blake-jenner-wanted-to-be-a-stand-up-comic |title=Glee Project's Blake Jenner Wanted To Be A Stand-Up Comic |date=August 27, 2013 |last=Gajewski |first=Ryan |website=[[Wetpaint]]}}</ref> he began [[Improvisational theatre|improvisation]] lessons<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2012/08/17/blake-jenner-glee-project-winner-interview |title=Glee Project Champ Blake Jenner |last=Slezak |first=Michael |date=August 17, 2012 |website=[[TVLine]]}}</ref> and participated in stage productions at the Roxy Performing Arts Center. In 2008, he became a member of \"Impromedy\", a [[sketch comedy]] improv group based in Miami.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://my.hsj.org/542122|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130921040813/http://my.hsj.org/542122|url-status=dead|archive-date=September 21, 2013 |title=Blake Jenner: A Varela alumnus' journey to 'Glee' |date=October 3, 2012 |last=Morales |first=Claudia |website=The Viper Vibe}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nEager to pursue a career in acting, Jenner left Miami and moved to [[Los Angeles]] after graduating high school a year early, with just $2,500.<ref name=\"TV Marti\"/><ref name=\"TV Marti\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://omg.yahoo.com/news/five-things-don-t-know-blake-jenner-215800656.html |title=Five Things You Don't Know About Blake Jenner |date=August 21, 2012 |last=Harrington |first=Amy and Nancy |website=[[Yahoo!]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130922191122/http://omg.yahoo.com/news/five-things-don-t-know-blake-jenner-215800656.html |archivedate=September 22, 2013 |df=}}</ref> While residing in California, he took on many jobs including a waiter, clothing store associate, and parrot salesman while auditioning for acting roles.<ref name=\"TV Marti\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wetpaint.com/glee/articles/glee-project-2-winner-blake-jenner-on-his-hopes-for-glee-season-4-and-meeting-damian-mcginty-exclusive |title=Glee Project 2 Winner Blake Jenner on His Hopes for Glee Season 4 |date=August 16, 2012 |last=Douglass |first=Beth |website=[[Wetpaint]]}}</ref> He continually attended improv classes at [[The Groundlings]], and eventually did a guest show with that company two years later.<ref>{{cite tweet |number=239123551121178624 |title=Blake Jenner learned the importance of comedic timing from improv classes with The Groundlings |user=groundlings |author=Groundlings |date=August 24, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.groundlings.com/performers/performer-details.aspx?performerID=515# |title=Performers: Blake Jenner |year=2012 |last=Groundlings |website=[[The Groundlings]] |access-date=September 21, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921060653/http://www.groundlings.com/performers/performer-details.aspx?performerID=515 |archive-date=September 21, 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nBy 2011, he was cast in the short films ''Wurlitzer'' and ''The Truth In Being Right'' and the horror film ''[[Cousin Sarah]]''. He also made a guest appearance on [[Freeform (TV channel)|ABC Family]]'s sitcom ''[[Melissa & Joey]]'' as Miller Collins.<ref>{{cite web |title=Who Is Glee's Blake Jenner? |url=http://www.wetpaint.com/who-is-glee-project-2-contender-blake-jenner-706179/|access-date=January 10, 2016 |website=[[Wetpaint]] |date=November 9, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, he was selected through industry channels to audition as one of 15 contestants on the second season of ''[[The Glee Project]]'', a television [[reality show]] for which the prize was a guaranteed seven-episode arc on the following season of ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]''. He was one of three finalists and ultimately won.<ref name=\"HR816\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/glee-project-winner-blake-jenner-glee-season-4-362655 |title=Winner Blake Jenner: 'I'd Love to Be a Finn-Type Character |first=Lesley |last=Goldberg |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=August 15, 2012|access-date=August 16, 2012 |quote=The 19-year-old...}}</ref> After appearing as Ryder Lynn on the fourth season of ''Glee'', he was later nominated and won the [[2013 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Award for Choice TV Breakout Star]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-207_162-57598050/teen-choice-awards-2013-list-of-winners |title=Teen Choice Awards 2013: List of winners |date=August 11, 2013 |last=Derschowitz |first=Jessica |website=[[CBS News]]}}</ref> Jenner, along with co-stars [[Jacob Artist]], [[Becca Tobin]], [[Alex Newell]], and [[Melissa Benoist]], was promoted to series regular status for the [[Glee (season 5)|fifth season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/glee-promotes-five-series-regulars-577552 |title='Glee' Promotes Five to Series Regulars (Exclusive) |date=June 29, 2013 |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref>\n\nIn the summer of 2013, Jenner wrote the screenplay for ''Billy Boy''. He and Benoist went on [[Kickstarter]] to ask fans to help fund the project's production; as of December 11, 2013, the project has reached its $100,000 goal. Jenner was subsequently cast in the horror film ''Within''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.joblo.com/horror-movies/news/phil-claydons-crawlspace-cast-grows-with-glee-star-blake-jenner |title=''Crawlspace'' cast grows with ''Glee'' star Blake Jenner |website=[[JoBlo.com]]|access-date=November 6, 2014 |date=March 25, 2014 |last=Walkuski |first=Eric}}</ref> In late 2015, Jenner was cast in a recurring role as Adam Foster on ''[[Supergirl (TV series)|Supergirl]]'', playing opposite his then-wife Melissa Benoist, who stars as the series' title character. His first appearance aired on January 25, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2015/11/18/supergirl-blake-jenner-cast-melissa-benoist-glee-reunion/ |title=Supergirl Stages Glee Reunion, Casts Blake Jenner as Kara's [Spoiler] |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |date=November 18, 2015 |website=[[TVLine]]|access-date=January 10, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Jenner starred as Jake Bradford in [[Richard Linklater]]'s comedy film ''[[Everybody Wants Some!! (film)|Everybody Wants Some!!]]'', which was released on March 30, and played [[Hailee Steinfeld]]'s character's brother in the coming-of-age drama ''[[The Edge of Seventeen]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last=A. Lincoln |first=Ross |title=Blake Jenner Joins Hailee Steinfeld In STX Coming-Of-Age Drama |url=http://deadline.com/2015/10/untitled-stx-drama-adds-glee-alum-blake-jenner-1201568151/|access-date=December 31, 2015 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=October 6, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2016, he was announced to have joined the cast of [[Shawn Christensen]]'s drama film ''[[The Vanishing of Sidney Hall]]'',<ref>{{cite web |last=Kroll |first=Justin |url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/blake-jenner-margaret-qualley-tim-blake-nelson-sidney-hall-1201759970/ |title=Blake Jenner, Margaret Qualley and Tim Blake Nelson Join 'Sidney Hall' (EXCLUSIVE) |date=April 25, 2016 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|access-date=April 25, 2016}}</ref> which premiered at the [[2017 Sundance Film Festival]] and was released on 2018.\n\nIn February 2017, he was announced to have joined the cast of Bart Layton's crime drama film ''[[American Animals]]''.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/blake-jenner-set-for-bart-laytons-american-animals-1201982884/ |title=Blake Jenner, Four Others Join Evan Peters in Indie Heist Film 'American Animals' |last=Mitchell |first=Robert |date=February 9, 2017 |work=Variety|access-date=June 28, 2018}}</ref> It premiered at the [[2018 Sundance Film Festival]] on January 19, 2018 and was released on June 1, 2018, by [[The Orchard (company)|The Orchard]] and [[MoviePass|MoviePass Ventures]].\n\nOn June 27, 2018, it was announced that Jenner will be playing Christian de Neuvillette in the [[Goodspeed Musicals|Goodspeed Musical production]]'s ''Cyrano'' at the [[Norma Terris Theatre]] from August 3 through September 9, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theatermania.com/connecticut-theater/news/blake-jenner-joins-musical-adaptation-of-cyrano_85701.html |title=Blake Jenner Joins Musical Adaptation of Cyrano at Goodspeed|access-date=June 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/connecticut/article/Goodspeed-Adds-8-Performances-Of-CYRANO-Due-to-Popular-Demand-20180712 |title=Goodspeed Adds 8 Performances Of CYRANO Due to Popular Demand |last=Desk |first=BWW News |work=BroadwayWorld.com|access-date=July 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2018, it was announced that Jenner had been cast as Sean in ''[[What/If]]'', [[Netflix]]'s anthology neo-noir thriller series.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2018/08/what-if-blake-jenner-star-netflix-social-thriller-series-renee-zellweger-1202455171/ |title=''What/If'': Blake Jenner To Star In Netflix Social Thriller Series |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=August 31, 2018 |work=Deadline|access-date=September 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn August 29, 2019, it was announced that Jenner would be starring in [[Richard Linklater]]'s film adaptation of [[Merrily We Roll Along (musical)|''Merrily We Roll Along'']], which would be shot over the course of twenty years. Principal photography of the first section of the film has already been completed. Jenner is set to star alongside [[Beanie Feldstein]] and [[Ben Platt (actor)|Ben Platt]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/richard-linklater-merrily-we-roll-along-20-year-film-production-1202707828/|title=Richard Linklater To Shoot Stephen Sondheim Musical \u2018Merrily We Roll Along\u2019 Over 20 Years For Blumhouse|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|last2=D'Alessandro|first2=Anthony|date=2019-08-30|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-08-30}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nJenner became engaged to his former ''Glee'' co-star [[Melissa Benoist]] in 2013<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/blake-jenner-melissa-benoist-engaged-glee-costars-set-to-tie-the-knot-2013117/ |title=Blake Jenner, Melissa Benoist Engaged: Glee Costars Set to Tie the Knot |date=July 12, 2013 |work=US Weekly |access-date=August 25, 2018 |first=Joyce |last=Chen}}</ref> and the pair reportedly married in 2015.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.eonline.com/news/675549/glee-s-melissa-benoist-and-blake-jenner-are-married |title=Glee's Melissa Benoist and Blake Jenner Are Married! |date=July 13, 2015 |work=E! Online|access-date=August 24, 2018}}</ref> However, that same year, Benoist commented that they had been married \"longer than anybody knows,\" with some sources claiming that the couple actually wed in 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.denverpost.com/2015/08/06/melissa-benoist-a-colorado-native-takes-flight-as-tvs-supergirl/ |title=Melissa Benoist, a Colorado native, takes flight as TV's 'Supergirl' |first=Joanne |last=Ostrow |work=[[Denver Post]] |location=Colorado |date=August 6, 2015 |accessdate=June 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"eonlinemarriage\">{{cite web |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/675549/glee-s-melissa-benoist-and-blake-jenner-are-married |title=Glee's Melissa Benoist and Blake Jenner Are Married! &#124; E! News |publisher=Eonline.com |date=July 13, 2015 |accessdate=January 1, 2017 |author=Toomey, Alyssa}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://pagesix.com/2017/12/21/supergirl-star-officially-split-from-husband-blake-jenner/ |title=\u2018Supergirl\u2019 star Melissa Benoist\u2019s marriage is over |website=[[Page Six]] |last=Burroni |first=Christine |date=December 21, 2017 |accessdate=August 31, 2018}}</ref> Benoist filed for divorce in late December 2016, citing irreconcilable differences,<ref name=\"People2016\">{{cite web |url=http://people.com/tv/melissa-benoist-files-for-divorce-blake-jenner-report/ |title=''Supergirl''{{'s}} Melissa Benoist Files for Divorce from Blake Jenner: Report|work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=December 29, 2016 | accessdate=January 3, 2017|last=Mizoguchi |first=Karen }}</ref> and the divorce was finalized in December 2017.<ref name=\"People2017\">{{cite web |url=http://people.com/tv/melissa-benoist-blake-jenners-finalize-divorce/ |title=''Supergirl''{{'s}} Melissa Benoist and Blake Jenner Finalize Divorce|work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=December 21, 2017 | accessdate=December 22, 2017|last=Dugan |first=Christina}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Fresh 2 Death''\n| Connor\n| Short film\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2011\n| ''Wurlitzer''\n| Alexander Moore\n| Short film; also producer\n|-\n| ''[[Cousin Sarah]]''\n| Brett Marks\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''The Truth In Being Right''\n| Jeffrey\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''Love at First Site''\n| Sydney Reynolds\n| Short film\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2016\n| ''[[Everybody Wants Some!! (film)|Everybody Wants Some!!]]''\n| Jake Bradford\n|\n|-\n| ''[[The Edge of Seventeen]]''\n| Darian Franklin\n|\n|-\n| ''Within''\n| Tommy \n| \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2017\n| ''[[The Vanishing of Sidney Hall]]''\n| Brett Newport\n| \n|-\n| ''[[Billy Boy (2017 film)|Billy Boy]]''\n| Billy Forsetti\n| Also writer and producer\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[American Animals]]''\n| Chas Allen\n| \n|-\n| TBA\n| ''[[Merrily We Roll Along (film)|Merrily We Roll Along]]''\n| Franklin Shepard\n| Will be filmed over 20 years\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Melissa & Joey]]''\n| Miller Collins\n| Episode: \"A House Divided\"\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[The Glee Project]]''\n| Himself \n| [[The Glee Project#Season two (2012)|Season 2]]\n|-\n| 2012\u201315\n| ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]''\n| [[Ryder Lynn]]\n| Main cast (season 5); recurring role (season 4); guest star (season 6)\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[MasterChef (U.S. TV series)|Master Chef]]''\n| Himself\n| Episode: \"Top 14 Compete\"\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Supergirl (TV series)|Supergirl]]''\n| Adam Foster \n| 2 episodes\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[What/If]]''\n|Sean\n|Main cast\n|}\n\n=== Video games ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2018\n|[[NBA 2K19]] \u2013 My Career Mode \n| Howie Carter\n| Voice and motion pictures<ref>{{Cite web |last=NBA 2K |title=NBA 2K19: The Way Back |date=August 21, 2018 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hlP0EBwLlhI|access-date=September 8, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cbssports.com/nba/news/nba-2k19-features-avengers-star-and-sixth-sense-kid-for-story-mode-where-you-battle-in-g-league/ |title='NBA 2K19' features 'Avengers' star and 'Sixth Sense' kid for story mode where you battle in G League |work=CBS Sports|access-date=September 8, 2018}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Stage==\n===Regional===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Venue\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Refs\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''Cyrano''\n| Christian de Neuvillette \n|[[Goodspeed Musicals|Goodspeed Musical]] production\n|<ref>Blake Jenner Joins Musical Adaptation of Cyrano at Goodspeed. (June 27, 2018) [https://www.broadwayworld.com/article/CYRANO-Starring-Peter-Dinklage-Finds-Full-Cast-20180627 CYRANO Starring Peter Dinklage Finds Full Cast; Blake Jenner and More.]</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Off-Broadway ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Venue\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Refs\n|-\n| 2019\n|''Cyrano''\n| Christian de Neuvillette\n|[[The New Group]] production\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/article/Full-Cast-Announced-for-Peter-Dinklage-Led-CYRANO-Grace-McLean-Jasmine-Cephas-Jones-and-More-20190813|title=Full Cast Announced for Peter Dinklage Led CYRANO; Grace McLean, Jasmine Cephas Jones, and More|last=Desk|first=BWW News|website=BroadwayWorld.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-14}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Work \n! Result\n|- \n| 2013\n| [[2013 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| Choice TV: Breakout Star\n| ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]''\n| {{won}}\n|- \n| 2017\n| [[San Diego Film Festival]]\n| Rising Star\n|\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|Glee discography}}\n* ''[[Glee: The Music Presents Glease]]''\n* ''[[Glee: The Music, Season 4, Volume 1]]''\n* ''[[Glee Sings the Beatles]]''\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n* {{Twitter}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jenner, Blake}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:American entertainers of Cuban descent]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male singers]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category: American male voice actors]]\n[[Category:Hispanic and Latino American male actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Miami]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Miami]]\n[[Category:Reality casting show winners]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actor and singer}}\n{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Blake Jenner \n| image = Blake Jenner 2013.jpg\n| caption = Jenner in 2013\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1992|8|27}}\n| birth_name = Blake Alexander Jenner\n| birth_place = [[Miami]], Florida, U.S.\n| spouse = [[Melissa Benoist]] ({{abbr|m.|married}} 2013 or 2015;{{efn|Sources disagree as to the year Jenner and Benoist were married. See [[#Personal life|\u00a7Personal life]]}} {{abbr|div.|divorced}} 2017)\n| occupation = {{Flatlist|\n* Actor\n* singer}}\n| years_active = 2010\u2013present\n}}\n'''Blake Alexander Jenner''' (born August 27, 1992)<ref name=\"TVG\">{{cite web |url=http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/blake-jenner/376096 |title=Blake Jenner |publisher=[[TV Guide|TVGuide.com]] |archivedate=May 29, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160529090948/http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/blake-jenner/376096}}</ref><!--Cited source, TV Guide, also confirmed full name Blake Alexander Jenner--> is an American actor and singer. Jenner won the second season of [[Oxygen (TV channel)|Oxygen]]'s ''[[The Glee Project]]'' and, as a result, portrayed [[Ryder Lynn]] on the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] musical comedy-drama series ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]''. He has since had starring and supporting roles in ''[[Everybody Wants Some!! (film)|Everybody Wants Some!!]]'' (2016), ''[[The Edge of Seventeen]]'' (2016), ''[[American Animals]]'' (2018), and ''[[What/If]]'' (2019).\n\n==Early life==\nJenner was born and raised in [[Miami]], Florida, the son of Mitzy and Richard Vernon Jenner. His father is of English, German and French-Canadian descent, and his mother is of Cuban descent, from a family from [[Santiago de Cuba]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mensfitness.com/life/entertainment/blake-jenner-all-american-leading-man-hollywood-needs-right-now-0 |title=Blake Jenner Is the All-American Leading Man Hollywood Needs Right Now |access-date=March 17, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317143927/http://www.mensfitness.com/life/entertainment/blake-jenner-all-american-leading-man-hollywood-needs-right-now-0 |archive-date=March 17, 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"TV Marti\">{{cite web |last=Barroso |first=Gina |title=TV Mart\u00ed Noticias \u2014 Blake Jenner: un joven cubanoamericano de Miami triunfa en Hollywood |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y_bBPQ27OYI |website=YouTube. TV Mart\u00ed Noticias|access-date=November 5, 2014 |language=Spanish |date=January 10, 2013}}</ref>\n\nHe grew up interested in music and film and began playing [[drums]] at age nine.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.miami.com/will-local-singeractor-win-glee-project-article |title=Local singer/actor Blake Jenner wins The Glee Project! |date=August 10, 2012 |last=Marr |first=Madeleine |website=Miami.com}}</ref> He attended [[Felix Varela High School]], where he joined the school's drama society Troupe 6162 and played varsity [[High school football|football]] and [[wrestling]]. Stating that he was \"in love with improv and comedy\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wetpaint.com/glee/articles/glee-projects-blake-jenner-wanted-to-be-a-stand-up-comic |title=Glee Project's Blake Jenner Wanted To Be A Stand-Up Comic |date=August 27, 2013 |last=Gajewski |first=Ryan |website=[[Wetpaint]]}}</ref> he began [[Improvisational theatre|improvisation]] lessons<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2012/08/17/blake-jenner-glee-project-winner-interview |title=Glee Project Champ Blake Jenner |last=Slezak |first=Michael |date=August 17, 2012 |website=[[TVLine]]}}</ref> and participated in stage productions at the Roxy Performing Arts Center. In 2008, he became a member of \"Impromedy\", a [[sketch comedy]] improv group based in Miami.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://my.hsj.org/542122|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130921040813/http://my.hsj.org/542122|url-status=dead|archive-date=September 21, 2013 |title=Blake Jenner: A Varela alumnus' journey to 'Glee' |date=October 3, 2012 |last=Morales |first=Claudia |website=The Viper Vibe}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nEager to pursue a career in acting, Jenner left Miami and moved to [[Los Angeles]] after graduating high school a year early, with just $2,500.<ref name=\"TV Marti\"/><ref name=\"TV Marti\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://omg.yahoo.com/news/five-things-don-t-know-blake-jenner-215800656.html |title=Five Things You Don't Know About Blake Jenner |date=August 21, 2012 |last=Harrington |first=Amy and Nancy |website=[[Yahoo!]] |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130922191122/http://omg.yahoo.com/news/five-things-don-t-know-blake-jenner-215800656.html |archivedate=September 22, 2013 |df=}}</ref> While residing in California, he took on many jobs including a waiter, clothing store associate, and parrot salesman while auditioning for acting roles.<ref name=\"TV Marti\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wetpaint.com/glee/articles/glee-project-2-winner-blake-jenner-on-his-hopes-for-glee-season-4-and-meeting-damian-mcginty-exclusive |title=Glee Project 2 Winner Blake Jenner on His Hopes for Glee Season 4 |date=August 16, 2012 |last=Douglass |first=Beth |website=[[Wetpaint]]}}</ref> He continually attended improv classes at [[The Groundlings]], and eventually did a guest show with that company two years later.<ref>{{cite tweet |number=239123551121178624 |title=Blake Jenner learned the importance of comedic timing from improv classes with The Groundlings |user=groundlings |author=Groundlings |date=August 24, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.groundlings.com/performers/performer-details.aspx?performerID=515# |title=Performers: Blake Jenner |year=2012 |last=Groundlings |website=[[The Groundlings]] |access-date=September 21, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130921060653/http://www.groundlings.com/performers/performer-details.aspx?performerID=515 |archive-date=September 21, 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nBy 2011, he was cast in the short films ''Wurlitzer'' and ''The Truth In Being Right'' and the horror film ''[[Cousin Sarah]]''. He also made a guest appearance on [[Freeform (TV channel)|ABC Family]]'s sitcom ''[[Melissa & Joey]]'' as Miller Collins.<ref>{{cite web |title=Who Is Glee's Blake Jenner? |url=http://www.wetpaint.com/who-is-glee-project-2-contender-blake-jenner-706179/|access-date=January 10, 2016 |website=[[Wetpaint]] |date=November 9, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, he was selected through industry channels to audition as one of 15 contestants on the second season of ''[[The Glee Project]]'', a television [[reality show]] for which the prize was a guaranteed seven-episode arc on the following season of ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]''. He was one of three finalists and ultimately won.<ref name=\"HR816\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/glee-project-winner-blake-jenner-glee-season-4-362655 |title=Winner Blake Jenner: 'I'd Love to Be a Finn-Type Character |first=Lesley |last=Goldberg |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=August 15, 2012|access-date=August 16, 2012 |quote=The 19-year-old...}}</ref> After appearing as Ryder Lynn on the fourth season of ''Glee'', he was later nominated and won the [[2013 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Award for Choice TV Breakout Star]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-207_162-57598050/teen-choice-awards-2013-list-of-winners |title=Teen Choice Awards 2013: List of winners |date=August 11, 2013 |last=Derschowitz |first=Jessica |website=[[CBS News]]}}</ref> Jenner, along with co-stars [[Jacob Artist]], [[Becca Tobin]], [[Alex Newell]], and [[Melissa Benoist]], was promoted to series regular status for the [[Glee (season 5)|fifth season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/glee-promotes-five-series-regulars-577552 |title='Glee' Promotes Five to Series Regulars (Exclusive) |date=June 29, 2013 |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref>\n\nIn the summer of 2013, Jenner wrote the screenplay for ''Billy Boy''. He and Benoist went on [[Kickstarter]] to ask fans to help fund the project's production; as of December 11, 2013, the project has reached its $100,000 goal. Jenner was subsequently cast in the horror film ''Within''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.joblo.com/horror-movies/news/phil-claydons-crawlspace-cast-grows-with-glee-star-blake-jenner |title=''Crawlspace'' cast grows with ''Glee'' star Blake Jenner |website=[[JoBlo.com]]|access-date=November 6, 2014 |date=March 25, 2014 |last=Walkuski |first=Eric}}</ref> In late 2015, Jenner was cast in a recurring role as Adam Foster on ''[[Supergirl (TV series)|Supergirl]]'', playing opposite his then-wife Melissa Benoist, who stars as the series' title character. His first appearance aired on January 25, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2015/11/18/supergirl-blake-jenner-cast-melissa-benoist-glee-reunion/ |title=Supergirl Stages Glee Reunion, Casts Blake Jenner as Kara's [Spoiler] |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |date=November 18, 2015 |website=[[TVLine]]|access-date=January 10, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Jenner starred as Jake Bradford in [[Richard Linklater]]'s comedy film ''[[Everybody Wants Some!! (film)|Everybody Wants Some!!]]'', which was released on March 30, and played [[Hailee Steinfeld]]'s character's brother in the coming-of-age drama ''[[The Edge of Seventeen]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last=A. Lincoln |first=Ross |title=Blake Jenner Joins Hailee Steinfeld In STX Coming-Of-Age Drama |url=http://deadline.com/2015/10/untitled-stx-drama-adds-glee-alum-blake-jenner-1201568151/|access-date=December 31, 2015 |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=October 6, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2016, he was announced to have joined the cast of [[Shawn Christensen]]'s drama film ''[[The Vanishing of Sidney Hall]]'',<ref>{{cite web |last=Kroll |first=Justin |url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/blake-jenner-margaret-qualley-tim-blake-nelson-sidney-hall-1201759970/ |title=Blake Jenner, Margaret Qualley and Tim Blake Nelson Join 'Sidney Hall' (EXCLUSIVE) |date=April 25, 2016 |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|access-date=April 25, 2016}}</ref> which premiered at the [[2017 Sundance Film Festival]] and was released on 2018.\n\nIn February 2017, he was announced to have joined the cast of Bart Layton's crime drama film ''[[American Animals]]''.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/blake-jenner-set-for-bart-laytons-american-animals-1201982884/ |title=Blake Jenner, Four Others Join Evan Peters in Indie Heist Film 'American Animals' |last=Mitchell |first=Robert |date=February 9, 2017 |work=Variety|access-date=June 28, 2018}}</ref> It premiered at the [[2018 Sundance Film Festival]] on January 19, 2018 and was released on June 1, 2018, by [[The Orchard (company)|The Orchard]] and [[MoviePass|MoviePass Ventures]].\n\nOn June 27, 2018, it was announced that Jenner will be playing Christian de Neuvillette in the [[Goodspeed Musicals|Goodspeed Musical production]]'s ''Cyrano'' at the [[Norma Terris Theatre]] from August 3 through September 9, 2018.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theatermania.com/connecticut-theater/news/blake-jenner-joins-musical-adaptation-of-cyrano_85701.html |title=Blake Jenner Joins Musical Adaptation of Cyrano at Goodspeed|access-date=June 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/connecticut/article/Goodspeed-Adds-8-Performances-Of-CYRANO-Due-to-Popular-Demand-20180712 |title=Goodspeed Adds 8 Performances Of CYRANO Due to Popular Demand |last=Desk |first=BWW News |work=BroadwayWorld.com|access-date=July 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2018, it was announced that Jenner had been cast as Sean in ''[[What/If]]'', [[Netflix]]'s anthology neo-noir thriller series.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2018/08/what-if-blake-jenner-star-netflix-social-thriller-series-renee-zellweger-1202455171/ |title=''What/If'': Blake Jenner To Star In Netflix Social Thriller Series |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=August 31, 2018 |work=Deadline|access-date=September 8, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn August 29, 2019, it was announced that Jenner would be starring in [[Richard Linklater]]'s film adaptation of [[Merrily We Roll Along (musical)|''Merrily We Roll Along'']], which would be shot over the course of twenty years. Principal photography of the first section of the film has already been completed. Jenner is set to star alongside [[Beanie Feldstein]] and [[Ben Platt (actor)|Ben Platt]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/richard-linklater-merrily-we-roll-along-20-year-film-production-1202707828/|title=Richard Linklater To Shoot Stephen Sondheim Musical \u2018Merrily We Roll Along\u2019 Over 20 Years For Blumhouse|last=D'Alessandro|first=Anthony|last2=D'Alessandro|first2=Anthony|date=2019-08-30|website=Deadline|language=en|access-date=2019-08-30}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nJenner became engaged to his former ''Glee'' co-star [[Melissa Benoist]] in 2013<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/blake-jenner-melissa-benoist-engaged-glee-costars-set-to-tie-the-knot-2013117/ |title=Blake Jenner, Melissa Benoist Engaged: Glee Costars Set to Tie the Knot |date=July 12, 2013 |work=US Weekly |access-date=August 25, 2018 |first=Joyce |last=Chen}}</ref> and the pair reportedly married in 2015.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.eonline.com/news/675549/glee-s-melissa-benoist-and-blake-jenner-are-married |title=Glee's Melissa Benoist and Blake Jenner Are Married! |date=July 13, 2015 |work=E! Online|access-date=August 24, 2018}}</ref> However, that same year, Benoist commented that they had been married \"longer than anybody knows,\" with some sources claiming that the couple actually wed in 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.denverpost.com/2015/08/06/melissa-benoist-a-colorado-native-takes-flight-as-tvs-supergirl/ |title=Melissa Benoist, a Colorado native, takes flight as TV's 'Supergirl' |first=Joanne |last=Ostrow |work=[[Denver Post]] |location=Colorado |date=August 6, 2015 |accessdate=June 18, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"eonlinemarriage\">{{cite web |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/675549/glee-s-melissa-benoist-and-blake-jenner-are-married |title=Glee's Melissa Benoist and Blake Jenner Are Married! &#124; E! News |publisher=Eonline.com |date=July 13, 2015 |accessdate=January 1, 2017 |author=Toomey, Alyssa}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://pagesix.com/2017/12/21/supergirl-star-officially-split-from-husband-blake-jenner/ |title=\u2018Supergirl\u2019 star Melissa Benoist\u2019s marriage is over |website=[[Page Six]] |last=Burroni |first=Christine |date=December 21, 2017 |accessdate=August 31, 2018}}</ref> Benoist filed for divorce in late December 2016, citing irreconcilable differences,<ref name=\"People2016\">{{cite web |url=http://people.com/tv/melissa-benoist-files-for-divorce-blake-jenner-report/ |title=''Supergirl''{{'s}} Melissa Benoist Files for Divorce from Blake Jenner: Report|work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=December 29, 2016 | accessdate=January 3, 2017|last=Mizoguchi |first=Karen }}</ref> and the divorce was finalized in December 2017.<ref name=\"People2017\">{{cite web |url=http://people.com/tv/melissa-benoist-blake-jenners-finalize-divorce/ |title=''Supergirl''{{'s}} Melissa Benoist and Blake Jenner Finalize Divorce|work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=December 21, 2017 | accessdate=December 22, 2017|last=Dugan |first=Christina}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Fresh 2 Death''\n| Connor\n| Short film\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2011\n| ''Wurlitzer''\n| Alexander Moore\n| Short film; also producer\n|-\n